  "text": "In children and adolescents, two reviews have been published. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] For Chinapaw et al., [CITATION_3] there is insufficient evidence for a longitudinal relationship between sedentary time and blood pressure or blood lipids. In contrast, Tremblay et al. [CITATION_4] reported that there is longitudinal evidence (studies with moderate quality) linking sedentary behavior (television, screen-time, and selfreported sedentary behavior) with total cholesterol and blood pressure; however, there was insufficient evidence for metabolic syndrome.",
